Founded in 1791, the Massachusetts Historical Society is an invaluable resource for American history, life, and culture. Its extraordinary collections tell the story of America through millions of rare and unique documents, artifacts, and irreplaceable national treasures. One of the nation’s most respected research libraries, the MHS holds more than 3,600 manuscript collections comprising in excess of 12 million document pages; personal and family papers constitute the core of the manuscript collection. Visitors can also enjoy public talks, tours, exhibitions, and scholarly seminars and conferences, and anyone can view selected digitized collections at <a href="https://www.masshist.org">www.masshist.org</a>.
